<a id="top"> </a><h1>Tenure-track Position, Trinity College</h1>
<p>
Trinity College seeks applications for a tenure-track assistant 
professor appointment in the Department of Philosophy with a start date 
of Fall 2012. 3/2 teaching load (reduced to 2/2 during first two years). 
Ph.D. required. AOS: contemporary analytic metaphysics and epistemology 
broadly construed (including, for example, Philosophy of Mind, 
Philosophy of Science or Philosophy of Language). AOC: open, but the 
department welcomes candidates with an interest in Analytic Feminist 
Philosophy and/or American Pragmatism. Trinity College is an Affirmative 
Action/Equal Opportunity Employer consistent with applicable federal 
and state law. Women and minorities are strongly encouraged to apply. 
Candidates should send a letter of application and CV, and should 
arrange for sending of a complete dossier including transcript, writing 
sample, evidence of teaching ability (such as syllabi and student 
evaluations) and at least three letters of recommendation. All materials 
should be sent to 
